<doc id="277868" wikidata="Q3422800" url="?curid=277868" title="Red Windsor (cheese)">
<text>Red Windsor is a pale cream English cheddar cheese from Leicestershire, made using pasteurised cow&#x27;s milk marbled with a wine, often a Bordeaux wine or a blend of port wine and brandy.

Red Windsor is produced by Long Clawson Dairy, based in Long Clawson, Leicestershire.

